user_comment: This classy vegan restaurant situated close to the Thi Nghe Canal was a pleasant surprise. The place has a very international feel, there are some nice eco-themed paintings on the ceiling and the waiters are really friendly. This is one of the better vegan places I visited during my 16 day trip to Vietnam A wide variety of vegan dishes, Vegan cheese and ice cream, Central location

user_comment: Not known too many, about 10-15mins from the heart of the city lies hidden an oasis for us city dweller. Khu du lá»‹ch VÄƒn ThÃ¡nh or VÄƒn ThÃ¡nh resort is nestled on a quite a sizeable piece of land about the size of 20 football fields which includes a man-made lake. During the evenings, this place provides a convenient escape from the noisy to tranquility. The dining area are in huts that extend into the lakes. So the dining ambience is wonderful especially with the gentle breeze that makes a relaxing and enjoyable experience. Our team chose a few dishes with our highlight being the hot pot. Food serve at VÄƒn ThÃ¡nh resort is mainly southern Vietnamese. The fried chicken wings in tamarid sauce was most memorable for us. Totally enjoyed every bite of it with the sauce which went well with our rice. The hot pot with our fish which we reckon was the tilapia fish. The soup and the fish were fantastic! Refreshing and fresh and most enjoyable under the stars by the lake. It is just unfortunate that most of the staff could not speak English. So we could not ask for recommended dishes. However, we encourage our foodie lovers to head down to this place when you have a special ocassion to celebrate with in a group or with family members. Food type and taste: Southern Vietnamese cuisine- 3/5 stars Price: Mid-range to high Ambience: Casual outdoor dining. Wonderful getaway from the city

user_titlec: Italian food from Italy but in Vietnam
user_comment: Came here for dinner with some friends. We were told that this place tasted like italian food from italy rather than north american italian food and boy did it live up to our expectations. The appetizers of antipasto was amazing. The fresh bread, olive oil and balsalmic vinegrette was just how i remembered eating it in Florence. My husband had the wagu beef steak and they cooked it perfectly the way he likes it (chicago blue rare) and i had the lamb popsicles for dinner (again cooked perfectly to medium well). We shared the spaghetti with clams and it was so yummy! We had chocolate cake and tiramisu for dessert which again was good. Overall, food was amazing, beautiful restaurant, friendly staff but you are paying north american prices for food. Would recommend coming here for special occasions or if youre in the mood to splurge on dinner.

If you're thinking of getting away from the usual crowded city buzz of Ho Chi Minh City, Binh Quoi Tourist Village offers the perfect retreat for a meal especially on a weekend. Located about 8-10km from the city centre, besides a quiet meal the place provides a refreshing and lush park for a therapeutic escape with nature. The restaurant is found the inner part of the park at where the small lake is. What is novel is the idea of fishing while dining over your meal. Bamboo fishing rods are available for rent and baits for sale. So this makes a wonderful getaway for family with kids where open spaces and nature are rather limited within and around the city area. The food served is nothing out-the-world but the usual local cuisine. But we recommend that you visit the place around 3-4pm. Take a walk and when the sun sets, buffet dining with cultural performances spring to live. Those activities are not available in the morning or afternoon. Food type and taste: Vietnamese cuisine - 3.5/5 stars Price: Mid-range Ambience: Casual dining. And fresh air for a change. Others: Excellent family dining getaway on a weekend.
